<!-- 48-HOUR EXEC SUMMARY -->
<div class="section">48-hour operational summary — 20 Mar 09:00 to 22 Mar 09:00</div>
<div class="card">
  <ul class="exec48">
    <li>
      <div class="exec-cat">
        <span class="exec-cat-title">Attack waves</span>
        <span class="exec-cat-val red">~155 total</span>
        <span class="exec-sub">Iran: ~55 · Hezbollah: ~100</span>
      </div>
      <div class="exec-body">
        <b>Iran (20–22 Mar):</b> Escalation sharply resumed after brief reduction. 10 salvos on Sunday alone (22 Mar). Multiple cluster barrage and ballistic missile waves. Iran targeted Dimona and Arad Saturday night — deliberately near Israel's nuclear research centre. Fragment from intercepted missile struck Old City Jerusalem (20 Mar). Cluster munitions hit Rishon LeZion daycare (21 Mar). IDF launched 200+ targets this weekend in Iran and struck Iranian weapon production sites overnight 22 Mar.<br>
        <b>Hezbollah (20–22 Mar):</b> ~100 waves. 19 people wounded in direct hits on northern border homes (21 Mar). Direct rocket strike in Kfar Vradim set a home on fire. Direct hit on a home in Ma'alot-Tarshiha. 15 wounded in 7 fragment impact sites in Tel Aviv/central Israel (22 Mar). Ayalon Highway missile fragment filmed in real time.<br>
        <span class="trend tr-up">↑ MAJOR ESCALATION</span> Weekend marked a dramatic reversal from the improving trend of 19–20 Mar. Iran achieved two consecutive interception failures in one night (Dimona, Arad). Both cities lacked adequate warning time. IDF ordered full investigation of air-defence failures. Education Minister cancelled school return nationwide.
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="exec-cat">
        <span class="exec-cat-title">Casualties (Israel, 48hrs)</span>
        <span class="exec-cat-val red">1 killed · 330+ wounded</span>
        <span class="exec-sub">Period total: 19+ killed · 4,080+ wounded</span>
      </div>
      <div class="exec-body">
        <b>Saturday night (21 Mar) — Dimona:</b> ~47 wounded (10-yr-old boy serious) · 1-storey building destroyed · After-school programme building collapsed · 33 treated at Soroka. <b>Saturday night (21 Mar) — Arad:</b> ~116 wounded (7 serious, 5-yr-old girl among seriously hurt) · Façades ripped off ≥10 apartment blocks, 3 in danger of collapse · Soroka declared mass casualty event · 36 still hospitalised (19 children) as of Sunday morning.<br>
        <b>Sunday (22 Mar) — Misgav Am:</b> Ofer Moskovitz, 60, kibbutz avocado farmer and community spokesman, killed when projectile hit his car. <b>Hezbollah claimed responsibility; IDF investigating if IDF mortar fire responsible</b> (no siren had sounded; artillery battery human error suspected). <b>Sunday — Central Israel:</b> 15 wounded in 7 fragment sites across Tel Aviv / central Israel.<br>
        <span class="trend tr-up">↑ CRITICAL</span> Netanyahu at Arad site: "Luckily, no one was killed in Arad and Dimona — but that's due to luck, not their intention." Arad Mayor: "all those in shelters were unharmed." IDF investigated both interception failures simultaneously. Nationwide school return cancelled. Health system declared full emergency mode. 36 still hospitalised (19 children) as of Sun morning.
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="exec-cat">
        <span class="exec-cat-title">Peak attack hours</span>
        <span class="exec-cat-val red">22:00 – 02:00</span>
        <span class="exec-sub">Sat night · Dimona hit ~22:00 · Arad hit ~23:30</span>
      </div>
      <div class="exec-body">
        <b>Saturday night (21 Mar):</b> Dimona struck first ~22:00 local · Arad struck ~23:30 — second interception failure in under 2 hours. Both missiles carried conventional warheads "with hundreds of kilograms of explosives" (IDF). Both missiles not intercepted. Iran separately fired at Eilat late Saturday — intercepted. <b>Sunday (22 Mar):</b> Hezbollah Misgav Am attack 08:00 local. Iranian 10-salvo barrage through Sunday morning. 15 wounded in Tel Aviv/central in morning fragment impacts.<br>
        <span class="trend tr-up">↑ NIGHT + DAYTIME DOUBLE PATTERN</span> Iran achieved two consecutive night-time interception failures and then pivoted to 10-salvo daytime campaign on Sunday. This dual-tempo pattern — heavy overnight strikes followed by sustained daytime pressure — is the most dangerous pattern observed to date and directly responsible for the highest 48-hour injury toll since Beit Shemesh (1 Mar).
      </div>
    </li>
    <li>
      <div class="exec-cat">
        <span class="exec-cat-title">Weapons &amp; targets</span>
        <span class="exec-cat-val red">Nuclear-site targeting</span>
        <span class="exec-sub">Dimona proximity · Arad residential · ICBMs to Diego Garcia</span>
      </div>
      <div class="exec-body">
        <b>Saturday nuclear targeting (21 Mar):</b> Iran targeted Dimona (Israel's nuclear research centre) — IAEA confirmed no facility damage, no radiation. Iran stated attack was retaliation for Israeli strike on Natanz. Iran's Parliament Speaker: "If Israel cannot intercept in Dimona, it is entering a new phase of the battle." IDF Chief says Iran fired a two-stage ICBM at Diego Garcia (Indian Ocean) — missiles can now reach Europe. UK bases targeted. <b>Cluster munitions (21 Mar):</b> Rishon LeZion daycare hit by cluster munitions (building damaged; no children present). Kfar Vradim home fire (direct rocket hit). Jerusalem Old City missile fragment (intercepted remnant).<br>
        <span class="trend tr-new">⚠ NEW PHASE SIGNAL</span> Iran's targeting of the Dimona nuclear research zone — plus first ICBM use at Diego Garcia — signals a doctrinal escalation to high-value symbolic and strategic targets. Trump threatened to "obliterate Iranian power plants" if Hormuz not reopened within 48hrs. Iran threatened to "completely shut" Hormuz in response. Nuclear site targeting, ICBM use, and Hormuz blockade together represent the most significant strategic escalation of the conflict to date.
      </div>
    </li>
