  {date:'22 Mar',loc:'Misgav Am (north) — under investigation',mun:'Hezbollah rocket OR IDF artillery (under investigation)',cas:'1 killed — Ofer Moskovitz, 60',fatal:true,mass:false,mx:370,my:50,ms:14,detail:'Ofer "Poshko" Moskovitz, 60, avocado farmer and Kibbutz Misgav Am spokesman, killed when projectile struck his car and set it on fire. Hezbollah claimed responsibility, saying it targeted soldiers. IDF immediately launched investigation into whether IDF mortar (122mm) was responsible — human error in artillery battery is the leading suspect. No siren had sounded before impact. IDF Northern Command, Air Force, and Artillery Corps all involved in investigation. Moskovitz had told Haifa radio 2 days earlier: "At any moment, a missile or drone could fall on me — this is Russian roulette." He was grandfather to a newborn a week old. Under investigation — cause not yet confirmed.'},
